2. Importing the dataset from training directory

In [2]:
batch_size = 64
imageSize = 64
target_dims = (imageSize, imageSize, 3)

train_dir = '/ich/ASL-Alphabat/datasets/ASL/asl_alphabet_train/'
CLASSES = ["A", "B", "C", "D", "E", "F", "G", "H", "I", "J", "K", "L", "M"]
num_classes = len(CLASSES)
train_len = 3000 * num_classes 

def get_data(folder):
    X = np.empty((train_len, imageSize, imageSize, 3), dtype=np.float32)
    y = np.empty((train_len,), dtype=int)
    cnt = 0
    for folderName in tqdm(os.listdir(folder), desc="Folder"):
        if not folderName.startswith('.'):
            label = CLASSES.index(folderName)
            for image_filename in tqdm(os.listdir(folder + folderName), desc=f"{folderName}", leave=False):
                img_file = cv2.imread(folder + folderName + '/' + image_filename)
                if img_file is not None:
                    img_file = skimage.transform.resize(img_file, (imageSize, imageSize, 3))
                    img_arr = np.asarray(img_file).reshape((-1, imageSize, imageSize, 3))
                    
                    X[cnt] = img_arr
                    y[cnt] = label
                    cnt += 1
    return X,y
X_train, y_train = get_data(train_dir)
print("Images successfully imported...")

5.2 Building model

In [12]:
model = Sequential()

model.add(Conv2D(32, (5, 5), input_shape=(64, 64, 3)))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))

model.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3)))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))

model.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3)))
model.add(Activation('relu'))
model.add(MaxPooling2D((2, 2)))

model.add(Flatten())

model.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))

model.add(Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax'))

model.summary()

5.3 Early Stopping and Compiling

5.3.1 Early Stopping¶

Early Stopping is done to make sure the model fitting stops at the most optimized accuracy point. After the early stopping point, the model might start overfitting. For testing purposes, this step can be skipped and complete training can be done.

In [13]:
from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping
early_stop = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=2)
5.3.2 Compiling¶
In [14]:
model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss='categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])

5.4 Model fitting

In [22]:
def show_images(images, width=5, height=5):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(width * 3, height * 3))
    fig.suptitle("ASL", fontsize=26)
    for idx, (image, title) in enumerate(images, 1):
        fig.add_subplot(width, height, idx)
        plt.imshow(image)
        plt.title(title)
        plt.axis("off")

    plt.show()
In [23]:
pr_result = []
for image, label in random.choices(test_dataset, k = 20):
    result = model.predict(np.asarray([image]), verbose=0)
    gt_pr_cls = np.asarray((CLASSES[np.argmax(label)], CLASSES[np.argmax(result)]))
    pr_result.append((image, f"GT: {gt_pr_cls[0]}, PR: {gt_pr_cls[1]}"))

show_images(pr_result)
